############### COMPILATION ##################
./compile_discoSnp++.sh

############### QUICK START ##################
 * WITHOUT mapping results on a reference genome:
       ./run_discoSnp++.sh -r "data_sample/reads_sequence1.fasta.gz data_sample/reads_sequence2.fasta.gz" -T
 * WITH mapping results on a reference genome:
       ./run_discoSnp++.sh -r "data_sample/reads_sequence1.fasta.gz data_sample/reads_sequence2.fasta.gz" -T  -G data_sample/reference_genome.fa 
       Warning: if bwa is not in you PATH, then add the option "-B path_to_bwa". For instance:    
       ./run_discoSnp++.sh -r "data_sample/reads_sequence1.fasta.gz data_sample/reads_sequence2.fasta.gz" -T  -G data_sample/reference_genome.fa -B /home/me/my_programs/bwa-0.7.12/

